PROJECT: College website + admin CMS

STACK
- Next.js 15 App Router
- React 18 + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Firebase Firestore
- Firebase Admin SDK
- Genkit/Gemini for AI

PURPOSE
Build a college website where admins can manage content without editing code.

PUBLIC FEATURES
- Home page
- Dynamic slug pages
- Departments
- Activities
- Faculty
- Admissions
- Events
- Gallery
- Contact
- Global header/footer
- Floating chatbot

ADMIN FEATURES
- Login with email + password
- Cookie-based admin session
- Dashboard tabs for homepage, pages, faculty, departments, activities, events, gallery, footer
- CRUD for structured content
- Drag/drop page ordering
- Drag/drop block ordering
- Toggle visibility

CORE CONTENT MODEL
1. pages
- title
- slug
- description
- visible
- order_position

2. blocks
- page_id
- type
- order_position
- visible
- data

3. departments
4. activities
5. team/faculty
6. events
7. gallery
8. footer
9. contact
10. announcements

PAGE BUILDER
- Pages are rendered from Firestore content blocks
- Supported block types: hero, text, image, announcements
- Homepage uses blocks
- Dynamic pages by slug use blocks

IMPORTANT APP FLOW
- `src/app/layout.tsx` loads header/footer and mounts chatbot
- `src/app/page.tsx` renders home blocks
- `src/app/[slug]/page.tsx` renders dynamic page blocks
- `src/components/HomeRenderer.tsx` and `src/components/PageRenderer.tsx` map block type to component
- `src/app/admin/page.tsx` is the main admin dashboard
- `src/components/admin/admin-page-editor.tsx` handles block editing/reordering

FIREBASE LAYER
- `src/firebase/server-init.ts` initializes Firebase Admin
- `src/firebase/services/pages.ts` handles pages CRUD + seeding + revalidation
- `src/firebase/services/blocks.ts` handles block CRUD + revalidation
- Other collections live in `src/firebase/services/*`

AUTH
- `src/app/login/actions.ts` checks allowed admin email + ADMIN_PASSWORD
- `middleware.ts` protects `/admin`
- Session is a cookie with value `1`

AI FEATURES
1. Chatbot
- UI: `src/components/chat/site-chatbot.tsx`
- Simple flow: `src/ai/flows/simple-gemini-chat.ts`
- Rich site-aware flow exists in `src/ai/flows/site-chat-flow.ts`

2. Program recommender
- UI: `src/components/admissions/program-recommender.tsx`
- Flow: `src/ai/flows/program-recommendation-tool.ts`

ENV VARS NEEDED
- ADMIN_PASSWORD
- NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_EMAIL or NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_EMAILS
- GEMINI_API_KEY
- GEMINI_MODEL
- FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY
- FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET / NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET

MINIMAL BUILD PROMPT
Create a production-ready college website and admin CMS using Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind, Firebase Firestore, Firebase Admin SDK, and Gemini/Genkit. Build a public website with pages for home, departments, activities, faculty, admissions, events, gallery, and contact. Build a protected admin dashboard that allows non-technical users to manage pages and modular content blocks, reorder content with drag and drop, manage faculty/departments/events/gallery/footer, and publish updates with cache revalidation. Add a floating AI chatbot and an admissions program recommender. Keep the UI responsive, professional, and CMS-driven.
